==English==

===Etymology===
[[Blend]] of '''[[crap]]''' and '''[[spectacular]]'''

===Adjective===
'''craptacular''' (''{{compar}}'' '''more craptacular''', ''{{superl}}'' '''most craptacular''')

#(''coarse UK slang'') Intended to be perceived as [[spectacular]], but actually perceived as extremely poor quality.
#:''Her essay was absolutely '''craptacular'''.''

====Quotations====
* '''2003,''' Deirdre Cowan Rice, ''The Family Jewels'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=hMGV_6Re_JAC&pg=PA39&lpg=PA39&sig=AdnBuVrq3TauxnZKC2yoneQSKRI]
*: For some reason, people think that if you give someone a present, that person has to listen to your '''craptacular''' advice or something, and swallow it with a smile.
* '''2004,''' Chris Turner, ''Planet Simpson,''
*: Homer has been known to sit on his couch excitedly clutching a pennant reading MID-SEASON, as he waits to drink in such '''craptacular''' Fox-TV [...]
* '''2004,''' T Mike Childs, ''Rocklopedia Fakebandica'' [http://books.google.com/books?ie=UTF-8&hl=en&id=Ogs6dQaSEZQC&pg=PA2&lpg=PA2&sig=8RTEANJCudztJgqLKOnkbpI6XEI]
